exif.ImageDescription: The headquarters of ReNew Power is located in Gurugram city (formerly Gurgaon) in the National Capital Region surrounding Delhi. The effects of Coronavirus-induced lockdown is still felt and seen. Delhi Metro's iconic Yellow Line services remain suspended since March 22nd. And the air quality is better than Delhiites have ever known it to be. Less than a year ago, the alarming levels of pollution in the capital forced the Supreme Court to reprimand the local government for inaction. Seen here: Aravali Biodiversity Park, Gurugram.

exif.ImageDescription: I was at a fair at Solidarity Park when I saw Ketsei arrive on his motorcycle. I mistook his bike to be a Harley-Davidson but it turned out to be a heavily modified Bajaj Avenger with a Harley logo stuck on to it. Ketsei is a dealer of motorcycle spares and accessories. He belongs to Angami tribe and lives in Kohima village, the original owners of the land on which the city stands today.

exif.ImageDescription: Naga Chili Eating Competition - While this annual competition art Hornbill Festival attracts many curious competitors and provides much entertainment, the Nagas take their chilli very seriously. In the end, the grand prize winner was a Naga man who came all the way from Tuensang. Immediately after their round, competitors are whisked away backstage where a medical team awaits them. They are given milk and cream to mitigate the burning sensation and their blood pressure is tested.

exif.ImageDescription: Ayodhya's new airport (about two weeks old) features motifs from the Indian epic Ramayana based on the life of Ram. In the background is a depiction of the scene when Ram returns with Sita to Ayodhya after a 14-year exile. In the foreground, a more mundane reality plays out. A couple is worried about their missing baggage. Others are struggling to fit the giant mural into their selfie or making calls to check on their airport pick-up.
